# Agent Behavior — SteadyStep

SteadyStep is a mobile-first demo prototype of a fall-prevention app for Swiss seniors 65+. It will be shown on a phone during a dinner meeting with a potential clinical co-founder. It must feel like a real app. No backend. All data mocked.

## Principles
1. Ship working code. Don't ask permission for obvious next steps.
2. Mobile-first. Every layout targets 390x844px. Desktop shows a centered phone frame.
3. Senior accessibility is mandatory: 14px minimum text, 48px tap targets, WCAG AA contrast.
4. No backend. All data from `src/data/`. No fetch, no localStorage for critical state.
5. Warm, not clinical. Companion app, not medical device UI.

## Execution
- Challenge bad ideas before implementing.
- Reuse before creating. Check existing components first.
- Components under 200 lines. One component per file.
- Functional components only, TypeScript strict, no `any`.
- Use `cn()` for conditional classnames.

## Never
- Inter, Roboto, Arial fonts
- Purple gradients or neon colors
- Hamburger menus, swipe-only navigation
- Spinners (use pulse animations)
- Bounce, shake, spin animations (vertigo risk)
- Placeholder Lorem Ipsum
